  "prompt": "Where can I get the solutions of resonance sheets and dpps?",
  "response": "For solutions to Resonance sheets and DPPs (Daily Practice Problems), you can try the following sources:\n\n1. **Resonance Institute's Official Resources**: Sometimes, Resonance might provide solutions to their study materials either through their official website or through direct purchase. It's best to check their official channels first.\n\n2. **Educational Forums and Websites**: Websites like Physics Forums, TopperLearning, or other educational platforms might have user-uploaded solutions or discussions around these problems. Be cautious about the accuracy of user-generated content.\n\n3. **Study Groups and Social Media**: Joining study groups on platforms like Telegram, WhatsApp, or even subreddits dedicated to entrance exam preparation can be helpful. Students often share solutions and resources within these communities.\n\n4. **YouTube Tutorials**: Some educators and ex-Resonance students might have created video solutions for these sheets on YouTube. Searching specifically for the module or DPP number might yield useful results.\n\n5. **Used Bookstores or Online Marketplaces**: Sometimes, solutions to past years' materials can be found in used bookstores or online marketplaces like OLX, Quikr, or even eBay.\n\n6. **Peer Sharing**: If you have friends or seniors who have completed these courses, they might have solutions that they can share with you.\n\nAlways ensure that you're using these resources ethically and in compliance with any copyright restrictions. Good luck with your studies!",
